<div id="review_3916950590" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3916950590" />
    <a title="Kelli" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4146551-kelli"><img alt="Kelli" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1413330332p2/4146551.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3916950590?book_show_action=true">Apr 14, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelli" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelli" href="/user/show/4146551-kelli">Kelli</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4146551-kelli?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4146551-kelli?shelf=not-fiction">not-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3916950590" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14706295385479167786">I&apos;m not sure there are appropriate adjectives to describe Bryan Stevenson. He is a selfless savior to Alabama&apos;s wrongly convicted death row inmates. He not only founded the Equal Justice Initiative and spent immeasurable hours/weeks/months/years working to exonerate those unfairly incarcerated, but his foundation also created The National Memorial for Peace and Justice and The Legacy Museum. Listening to this book, I was blown away by ALL of these scenarios that ended in death row incarcerations</span>
  <span id="freeText14706295385479167786" style="display:none">I'm not sure there are appropriate adjectives to describe Bryan Stevenson. He is a selfless savior to Alabama's wrongly convicted death row inmates. He not only founded the Equal Justice Initiative and spent immeasurable hours/weeks/months/years working to exonerate those unfairly incarcerated, but his foundation also created The National Memorial for Peace and Justice and The Legacy Museum. Listening to this book, I was blown away by ALL of these scenarios that ended in death row incarcerations. I was humbled by and in awe of all that Bryan Stevenson has accomplished, and I was deeply saddened by the reality presented. What is wrong with this country? How can people be convicted in a court of law when there is overwhelming evidence to prove their innocence? Why is it so disproportional? My heart hurts.<br /><br />My takeaway from my little suburban bubble in Massachusetts is that while we can't all be Bryan Stevensons, we can all participate in being part of the solution. For me that means putting this book in the hands of my children, checking my own self at the door every day, and continuing to raise my children to respect differences by honoring that we are all brothers and sisters and by teaching them true history. 5 stars<br /><br /><br /><b>EJI is committed to ending mass incarceration and excessive punishment in the United States, challenging racial and economic injustice, and protecting basic human rights for the most vulnerable people in American society.</b><br /><br />I know where I'm making charitable donations this year.<br /><br /><br /><a href="" rel="nofollow noopener">https://support.eji.org/</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="14706295385479167786" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3916950590">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
